# Page-Flip 3D Transform Constraint

## DO NOT change these two things — they prevent a page flash bug during flip animations:

### 1. CSS: `transform-style: flat` on `.stf__item`
In `src/index.css`, the rule `.album-flipbook .stf__item` MUST include:
```css
transform-style: flat !important;
```
The page-flip library sets `transform-style: preserve-3d` on `.stf__item`. If children have 3D-capable transforms (like `scaleX(-1)`), they become separate 3D entities that bypass the parent's `backface-visibility: hidden` during `rotateY` flip animations — causing the destination page to flash through the flipping page.

### 2. SpreadPage inner wrapper structure
In `SpreadPage.tsx`, the outer ref div (`ref={ref}`) MUST remain bare (no inline styles). All visual styles (`backgroundColor`, `overflow: hidden`, `transform: scaleX(-1)`) MUST live on the inner wrapper div — NOT on the ref div.

Why: `react-pageflip` overwrites the ref element's `style.cssText` every animation frame via `simpleDraw()` / `drawHard()`. Any React inline styles on the ref are wiped immediately.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div ref={ref} data-density="hard">
  <div style={{ backgroundColor, overflow: 'hidden', transform: 'scaleX(-1)' }}>
    {/* content */}
  </div>
</div>

// ❌ WRONG — styles on ref will be wiped by page-flip
<div ref={ref} data-density="hard" style={{ backgroundColor, transform: 'scaleX(-1)' }}>
  {/* content */}
</div>
```

### 3. DO NOT add `backfaceVisibility: hidden` to the inner wrapper
The `scaleX(-1)` on the inner wrapper can cause GPU rendering artifacts when combined with `backface-visibility: hidden` during the parent's 3D rotation — making the page momentarily transparent and exposing destination content. The `transform-style: flat` override on `.stf__item` is the sole correct fix.
